questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Arrange the following in correct sequence:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;A. Income under the different heads of income.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;B. Deduction from gross total income.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;C. Adjustment of losses of the current year and earlier years.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;D. Rounding off.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;Choose the correct answer from the options given below&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/quesImage56.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 1:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Compute the income of an individual under 5 heads of income on the basis of his residential status.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 2:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The income of any other person, if includible u/s&amp;nbsp;60 to 64, will be included under respective heads.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 3:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Set off of the losses if permissible, while aggregating the income under 5 heads of income.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 4:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Carry forward and set off of the losses of past years, if permissible, from such income.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 5:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The income computed under Steps 1 to 4 is known as Gross Total Income from which deductions under sections 80C to 80U (Chapter VIA) will be allowed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;However, no deduction under these sections will be allowed from short-term capital gain covered under section 111A, any long-term capital gain and winning of lotteries, etc., though these incomes are part of gross total income.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 6:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The balance income after allowing the deductions is known as total income which will be rounded off to the nearest Rs. 10.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 7:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Compute tax on such Total Income at the prescribed rates of tax.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 8:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Allow rebate of maximum Rs. 2,500 under section 87A in case of a resident individual having total income up to Rs. 3,50,000. For details see below.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 9:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Add surcharge @ 10% on total income exceeding Rs. 50,00,000 and up to Rs. 1 crore and 15% of such income-tax in case of an individual having a total income exceeding Rs. 1 crore.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 10:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Add education cess @ 2% and SHEC @ 1% on the tax (including surcharge if applicable).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 11:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Allow relief under section 89, if any.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 12:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Deduct the TDS, advance tax paid for the relevant assessment year, and double taxation relief under section 90, 90A, or 91.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The balance is the net tax payable which will be rounded of the nearest ten rupees and must be paid as self-assessment tax before submitting the return of income. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the correct sequence is:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Income under the different heads of income.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Adjustment of losses of the current year and earlier years.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Deduction from gross total income.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Rounding off.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Which two of the following are correct in terms of rate of tax deduction at source (TDS)?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a) Income by way of winning from horse race: @ 30%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b) Insurance Commission: @ 10%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;c) Rent of Plant &amp;amp; Machinery @ 5%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;d) Rent of furniture: @ 5%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Choose the correct option from the following:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TAX DEDUCTED AT SOURCE (TDS):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(251, 251, 251);&quot;&gt;The concept of TDS was introduced with an aim to collect tax from the very source of income. As per this concept, a person (deductor) who is liable to make payment of specified nature to any other person (deductee) shall deduct tax at source and remit the same into the account of the Central Government.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/quesImage56.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p id=&quot;TDS-Rates-under-Section-194I&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700; line-height: normal;&quot;&gt;TDS Rates under Section 194I:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rates of the tax deduction&amp;nbsp;depend on the nature of payment and are given below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;width: 350px;&quot; width=&quot;718&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type of Income&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TDS Rate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Income by way of winning from horse race&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;30% TDS&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Insurance Commission&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;5% TDS&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Rent of Plant &amp;amp; Machinery&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;2% TDS&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Rent of land, furniture, fitting, or building to HUF or individual&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;10% TDS&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Rent of land, furniture, or building to other than HUF or an individual&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;10% TDS&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/quesImage534.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Under Section 194-I&lt;/strong&gt;, rent on Land or building or furniture or fitting is 10%, however, the Official question of UGC has mentioned it as 5% and considered the option to be correct.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Which two of the following are correct about TDS certificates?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;A. TDS on salary payment - Form 16&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;B. TDS on non-salary payment - Form 16A&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;C. TDS on rent - Form 16B&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;D. TDS on sale of property - Form 16C&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;Choose the correct option:&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The term &amp;quot;TDS&amp;quot; refers to&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;Tax Deduction at Source&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;. It is a mechanism wherein a person who is responsible to pay a sum of specified nature shall deduct an amount towards TDS and pay it to the credit of the Central Government.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/quesImage56.png&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:350px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;thead&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;th scope=&quot;col&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Form No.&lt;/th&gt;
			&lt;th scope=&quot;col&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;TDS Certificate&lt;/th&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/thead&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Form 16&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;ul&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Form 16 is a TDS on salary payment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;If income from salary in a financial year is more than the basic exemption limit of Rs. 2,50,000, then the employer is required to deduct TDS on salary and deposit it with the government.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;/ul&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Form 16A&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;ul&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Form 16A is a TDS on non-salary payment&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;It is a certificate to endorse the amount of TDS for individuals whose earnings are generated from non-salary incomes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;/ul&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Form 16B&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;ul&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;Form 16B&amp;nbsp;is the TDS on sale of property.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;It is issued by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;the deductor i.e. buyer&amp;nbsp;of a property&amp;nbsp;to the deductee i.e. seller&amp;nbsp;of a property&amp;nbsp;in respect of the tax deducted and&amp;nbsp;deposited into the Government account.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;/ul&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Form 16C&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;ul&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;Form 16C is the TDS on rent&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;to be issued by the deductor i.e. tenant of a property&amp;nbsp;to the deductee i.e. landlord of a property&amp;nbsp;in respect of the tax deducted and deposited u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;nder section 194-IB of the Income-tax Act, 1961.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;/ul&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, statements A and B only are correct about the TDS certificates.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;!-- x-tinymce/html --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Match the LIST-I with LIST-II&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;width:330px;&quot; width=&quot;330&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot; style=&quot;width:151px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LIST - I&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;(Sections)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot; style=&quot;width:179px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LIST - II&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;(TDS)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:28px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;A.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:123px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:6.95pt;&quot;&gt;Section 194 of the Income Tax Act, 1961&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:28px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;I.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:151px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:7.05pt;&quot;&gt;Payment on account of&amp;nbsp;repurchase of units by mutual fund&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:28px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;B.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:123px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:6.95pt;&quot;&gt;Section 194C of the Income Tax Act, 1961&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:28px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;II.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:151px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:7.05pt;&quot;&gt;Payment to the non resident sportsman&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:28px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;C.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:123px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:6.95pt;&quot;&gt;Section 194E of the Income Tax Act, 1961&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:28px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;III.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:151px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:7.05pt;&quot;&gt;Payment to contractor and sub-contractor&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:28px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;D.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:123px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:6.95pt;&quot;&gt;Section 194F of the Income Tax Act, 1961&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:28px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;IV.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:151px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:7.05pt;&quot;&gt;Dividend&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
